## What is a recursive function

The definition and uses of a recursive function. Recursion is the procedure of defining a function in terms of itself. For example the factorial function can be defined, like any function, by choosing an object and a procedure for determining the value of the object given the value of the object, this latter object, and the operation chosen to determine the value of the object from the value of an object and the operation chosen to obtain that object's value from the object's value, and so on and so forth. One method for doing this is to let f(x) be the object (that was previously defined by the chosen procedure) and f(x) the result of the procedure.

